headline: Disney earnings, Fedspeak, mortgage rates: What to Watch
summary: Disney (DIS) will release its fiscal fourth quarter earnings results tomorrow morning, before the market open. Other notable companies reporting quarterly results include Applied Materials (AMAT), Oklo Inc. (OKLO), and JD.com (JD). Commentary is expected out from Federal Reserve Chair Jerome Powell, Fed Governor Adriana Kugler, and New York Fed President John Williams on Thursday, November 14. Lastly, October's Producer Price Index (PPI) and this week's mortgage rate readings are due out as well. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.
